AI behavior design

What the AI should do

The AI should not just praise or nag. It should do these jobs:

1. Detect patterns

Examples:
	•	“Your best idea production happens after 2 PM on days with movement before noon.”
	•	“You start too many branches when uncertainty rises.”
	•	“Public shipping improves motivation more than private planning.”

2. Predict drift

Examples:
	•	“At current pace, sleep debt will cut productivity by Thursday.”
	•	“Project completion odds drop when more than 4 active threads are open.”

3. Offer advice in layers

Not one giant lecture. Advice should come in levels:
	•	Micro: what to do now
	•	Tactical: what to adjust this week
	•	Strategic: what pattern to change this month
	•	Narrative: what story you are currently living

4. Reframe setbacks

The board should translate failure into signal.

Not:
	•	“You failed your goal.”

But:
	•	“Completion fell because energy and task granularity got misaligned.”

That keeps the system useful instead of moralizing.

