⸻

Scoring model

Each domain gets a score from 0–100 based on:

score = progress + consistency + trend + alignment - friction

Where:
	•	progress = how much moved
	•	consistency = repeated effort
	•	trend = slope improving or declining
	•	alignment = does behavior match stated goals
	•	friction = blockers, overload, sleep debt, fragmentation

That way the board rewards real motion, not fantasy.

⸻

Advice engine logic

Daily advice formula

The system should generate advice from:
	•	current state
	•	recent trend
	•	bottleneck
	•	opportunity
	•	user’s stated priorities

Template:

State: what’s happening
Cause: likely reason
Advice: smallest useful move
Risk if ignored: what drift may occur

Example:

State: Build output is down 18% over 4 days.
Cause: too many concurrent idea branches.
Advice: freeze new branches for 24 hours and close one visible task.
Risk if ignored: motivation turns abstract and loops stay open.

